\f0\b Core Idea:
\f1\b0 \
At first glance, \'93The pile is the plan\'94 seems counterintuitive. A pile often represents chaos, disorganization, and a lack of structure\'97everything that a plan is supposed to counteract. Yet, this statement reframes the pile not as a problem but as an active and inherent part of planning itself. The pile is both the 
\f0\b manifestation
\f1\b0  and the 
\f0\b potential
\f1\b0  of the plan in formation.\
\

